gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: CTD - ODF/SIOR Bottle Dataset Description: <p>CTD bottle data from 30-ODF/SIOR (Ocean Data Facility 12 bottle, 30 liter Niskin rosette) GT10 Transect.</p><p>&nbsp;</p> Acquisition Description: <p>&quot;Filtered samples for non-contamination prone elements were collected from the ODF Niskin rosette (12 x 30L Niskin bottles) using AcroPak 500 filter cartridges with a Supor 0.45/0.8&mu;m membrane attached to Teflon-lined Tygon tubing.&quot; (from KN199-04 cruise report)</p><p>Refer to <a target="_blank" href="http://bcodata.whoi.edu//US_GEOTRACES/AtlanticSection/Cruise_Report_for_Knorr_199_Final_v3.pdf">KN199-04 Cruise Report</a> (PDF) for detailed descriptions of acquisition and processing methodologies.</p>

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: GEOTRACES is a SCOR sponsored program; and funding for program infrastructure development is provided by the U.S. National Science Foundation.GEOTRACES gained momentum following a special symposium, S02: Biogeochemical cycling of trace elements and isotopes in the ocean and applications to constrain contemporary marine processes (GEOSECS II), at a 2003 Goldschmidt meeting convened in Japan. The GEOSECS II acronym referred to the Geochemical Ocean Section Studies To determine full water column distributions of selected trace elements and isotopes, including their concentration, chemical speciation, and physical form, along a sufficient number of sections in each ocean basin to establish the principal relationships between these distributions and with more traditional hydrographic parameters;* To evaluate the sources, sinks, and internal cycling of these species and thereby characterize more completely the physical, chemical and biological processes regulating their distributions, and the sensitivity of these processes to global change; and* To understand the processes that control the concentrations of geochemical species used for proxies of the past environment, both in the water column and in the substrates that reflect the water column.GEOTRACES will be global in scope, consisting of ocean sections complemented by regional process studies. Sections and process studies will combine fieldwork, laboratory experiments and modelling. Beyond realizing the scientific objectives identified above, a natural outcome of this work will be to build a community of marine scientists who understand the processes regulating trace element cycles sufficiently well to exploit this knowledge reliably in future interdisciplinary studies.

gmd:descriptor.gco:CharacterString: PI-supplied Description: Expedition code assigned by the CCHDO: NODCShipCodeYearMonthDay; General Description: dataset_id: a unique combination of alpha and/or numeric characters designating a dataset (filename in many cases)

PI-supplied Description: Synonym for cruise.; General Description: The cruise_name is a local name chosen by project investigators for a research expedition on a vessel, as opposed to the formal/official cruise ID asserted by the vessel operator.
PI-supplied Description: Station number.; General Description: consecutive station number
PI-supplied Description: Cast number.; General Description: cast or profile number

PI-supplied Description: GEOTRACES Event Number.; General Description: event or operation number; often derived from date/time (MMDDHHmm) of sampling and when combined with year (YYYY) is a unique sampling identifier/data processing key. Date/time is not necessarily in GMT.

PI-supplied Description: Date (UTC).; General Description: UTC month, day and year, usually as a text string, e.g. feb10_1995. It is better to use one of the other forms of presenting date and time data so that the data can be used in computations and for comparisons. Note, if the string begins with numbers but also includes letters, there may be problems using the field name for retrieval. Use date_gmt for future data sets.
PI-supplied Description: Time (UTC).; General Description: UTC time, using 2400 clock format

PI-supplied Description: Latitude (South is negative).; General Description: latitude, in decimal degrees, North is positive, negative denotes South; Reported in some datasets as degrees, minutes NERC Description: The angular distance north or south from the equator, measured along the meridian of the point of interest.

PI-supplied Description: Longitude (West is negative).; General Description: longitude, in decimal degrees, East is positive, negative denotes West; Reported in some datsets as degrees, minutes NERC Description: The angular distance east or west east or west of Greenwich to the point of interest.

PI-supplied Description: GEOTRACES sample number.; General Description: unique sample identification or number; any combination of alpha numeric characters; precise definition is file dependent NERC Description: Data record, event, sample or measurement reference numbers

PI-supplied Description: Sample number.; General Description: unique sample identification or number; any combination of alpha numeric characters; precise definition is file dependent NERC Description: Data record, event, sample or measurement reference numbers
PI-supplied Description: Bottle identification number.; General Description: water bottle number, generally assigned to a position on a CTD rosette, identifies all samples drawn from a given bottle

PI-supplied Description: Bottle quality flag.; General Description: Data flag. Multiple uses which are dataset dependent. Some uses: data quality, collection occurance or success, depth indicator. See dataset documentation for specific details

PI-supplied Description: Bottle sampling date.; General Description: date; generally reported in GMT as YYYYMMDD (year; month; day); also as MMDD (month; day); EqPac dates are local Hawaii time NERC Description: Unavailable

PI-supplied Description: Bottle collection time.; General Description: Time GMT defined as HHMM; time of day; generally reported in GMT as HHMM (hours and minutes) but may also be HH.H (decimal hours) or HHMMSS (hours; minutes and seconds); in EqPac time is reported as Hawaii local time NERC Description: Time elapsed between 00:00 UT on the date of the event of interest and that event.

PI-supplied Description: Bottle latitude (South is negative).; General Description: latitude, in decimal degrees, North is positive, negative denotes South; Reported in some datasets as degrees, minutes NERC Description: The angular distance north or south from the equator, measured along the meridian of the point of interest.

PI-supplied Description: Bottle longitude (West is negative).; General Description: longitude, in decimal degrees, East is positive, negative denotes West; Reported in some datsets as degrees, minutes NERC Description: The angular distance east or west east or west of Greenwich to the point of interest.
PI-supplied Description: Bottom depth.; General Description: water depth, in meters

gco:attributeType.xlink:title: Pressure (spatial co-ordinate) exerted by the water body by profiling pressure sensor and corrected to read zero at sea level

gmd:descriptor.gco:CharacterString: PI-supplied Description: CTD pressure.; General Description: water pressure at measurement; depth reported as pressure; positive number increasing with water depth NERC Description: The force per unit area exerted by the water column on a mobile sensor located in the water column.

PI-supplied Description: CTD depth.; General Description: observation/sample depth, in meters; best estimate; usually but not always calculated from pressure; calculated either from CTD pressure using Fofonoff and Millard (1982; UNESCO Tech Paper #44) algorithm adjusted for 1980 equation of state for seawater (EOS80) or simply equivalent to nominal depth as recorded during sampling if CTD pressure was unavailable NERC Description: The distance of a sensor or sampling point below the sea surface.

PI-supplied Description: CTD temperature.; General Description: water temperature at measurement depth NERC Description: The degree of hotness at any position within a volume of fresh or salt water expressed against the International Temperature Scale 1990 (ITS-90) calibration standard.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: <p>&quot;Filtered samples for non-contamination prone elements were collected from the ODF Niskin rosette (12 x 30L Niskin bottles) using AcroPak 500 filter cartridges with a Supor 0.45/0.8&mu;m membrane attached to Teflon-lined Tygon tubing.&quot; (from KN199-04 cruise report)</p><p>Refer to <a target="_blank" href="http://bcodata.whoi.edu//US_GEOTRACES/AtlanticSection/Cruise_Report_for_Knorr_199_Final_v3.pdf">KN199-04 Cruise Report</a> (PDF) for detailed descriptions of acquisition and processing methodologies.</p>

<p>Refer to <a href="http://bcodata.whoi.edu//US_GEOTRACES/AtlanticSection/Cruise_Report_for_Knorr_199_Final_v3.pdf" target="_blank">KN199-04 Cruise Report</a> (PDF) for detailed descriptions of acquisition and processing methodologies.</p><p>Note: 'FLAG_W' columns = WHP (<a target="_blank" href="http://woce.nodc.noaa.gov/woce_v3/wocedata_1/whp/exchange/exchange_format_desc.htm">WOCE Hydrographic Program</a>) quality flags.</p><p>Processing Notes:<br />13 Feb 2013: BCO-DMO corrected the event numbers of several CTD casts. The correct event numbers were verified in the original cast sheets. Edits made:<br />Changed event number of station 2 cast 1 from 2022 to 2042;<br />Changed event number of station 4 cast 1 from 2024 to 2072;<br />Changed event number of station 5 cast 4 from 2075 to 2091;<br />Changed event number of station 7 cast 6 from 2107 to 2132;<br />Changed event number of station 9 cast 1 from 2009 to 2162;<br />Changed event number of station 9 cast 3 from 2059 to 2165.</p><p>The restriction on this dataset was removed according to instructions from the Chief Scientist, April 26, 2013.</p>

gmi:description.gco:CharacterString: PI Supplied Instrument Name: GO-FLO Bottle Instrument Name: GO-FLO Bottle Instrument Short Name:GO-FLO Instrument Description: GO-FLO bottle cast used to collect water samples for pigment, nutrient, plankton, etc. The GO-FLO sampling bottle is specially designed to avoid sample contamination at the surface, internal spring contamination, loss of sample on deck (internal seals), and exchange of water from different depths. Community Standard Description: http://vocab.nerc.ac.uk/collection/L05/current/30/

PI Supplied Instrument Name: Niskin bottle Instrument Name: Niskin bottle Instrument Short Name:Niskin bottle Instrument Description: A Niskin bottle (a next generation water sampler based on the Nansen bottle) is a cylindrical, non-metallic water collection device with stoppers at both ends. The bottles can be attached individually on a hydrowire or deployed in 12, 24 or 36 bottle Rosette systems mounted on a frame and combined with a CTD. Niskin bottles are used to collect discrete water samples for a range of measurements including pigments, nutrients, plankton, etc. Community Standard Description: http://vocab.nerc.ac.uk/collection/L22/current/TOOL0412/
